SIMPLE: mutton
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mutton
<hw>Mut"ton</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>motoun</ets>, OF. <ets>moton</ets>, <ets>molton</ets>, a sheep,
wether, F. <ets>mouton</ets>, LL. <ets>multo</ets>, by transposition of
<it>l</it> fr. L. <ets>mutilus</ets> mutilated. See
<er>Mutilate</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A sheep.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Chapman.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Not so much ground as will feed a <qex>mutton</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Sir H. Sidney.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Muttons</qex>, beeves, and porkers are good old words for the
living quadrupeds.</q> <rj><qau>Hallam.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The flesh of a sheep.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The fat of roasted <qex>mutton</qex> or beef.</q>
<rj><qau>Swift.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A loose woman; a prostitute.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<cs><p><col><b>Mutton bird</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>the
Australian short-tailed petrel (<spn>Nectris brevicaudus</spn>).</cd> --
<col><b>Mutton chop</b></col>, <cd>a rib of mutton for broiling, with
the end of the bone at the smaller part chopped off.</cd> --
<col><b>Mutton fish</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>the American
eelpout. See <er>Eelpout</er>.</cd> -- <col><b>Mutton fist</b></col>,
<cd>a big brawny fist or hand.</cd> <mark>[Colloq.]</mark>
<au>Dryden.</au> -- <col><b>Mutton monger</b></col>, <cd>a pimp.</cd>
<mark>[Low & Obs.]</mark> <au>Chapman.</au> -- <col><b>To return to
one's muttons</b></col>. <ety>[A translation of a phrase from a farce by
<person>De Brueys</person>, <ets>revenons ⟦agrave⟧ nos moutons</ets> let
us return to our sheep.]</ety> <cd>To return to one's topic, subject of
discussion, etc.</cd> <mark>[Humorous]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I willingly <qex>return to my muttons</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>H. R.
Haweis.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p></cs>

<p><ent>muttonfish</ent>⟦br⟧
